1
00:00:00,340 --> 00:00:01,740
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:01,740 --> 00:00:03,440
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,440 --> 00:00:05,140
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:06,850 --> 00:00:08,310
(Episode 7)

5
00:00:26,260 --> 00:00:28,030
So we meet again.

6
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:33,170
I'm sorry it took all this trouble
just for us to meet.

7
00:00:33,240 --> 00:00:34,240
That's all right.

8
00:00:34,870 --> 00:00:37,680
Yoon Jung filled me in
on what happened.

9
00:00:38,110 --> 00:00:40,450
I should apologize
for insisting on meeting.

10
00:00:40,650 --> 00:00:41,650
But I did so...

11
00:00:41,650 --> 00:00:44,780
because there's something
I need to tell you.

12
00:00:45,450 --> 00:00:48,490
So you did have something
to tell me.

13
00:00:52,560 --> 00:00:53,630
I have...

14
00:00:54,590 --> 00:00:57,030
evidence from the past incident.

15
00:01:02,700 --> 00:01:05,340
I have it all,
from evidence of the murder...

16
00:01:05,470 --> 00:01:06,910
to the killer's bloodstains.

17
00:01:07,410 --> 00:01:09,040
You'll finally be able to prove...

18
00:01:09,810 --> 00:01:11,610
who killed your sister.

19
00:01:14,180 --> 00:01:16,650
How could the evidence still exist?

20
00:01:17,350 --> 00:01:20,550
I was sure they took it
from your office.

21
00:01:20,990 --> 00:01:22,690
They probably did.

22
00:01:22,790 --> 00:01:23,890
However,

23
00:01:24,560 --> 00:01:26,990
I'd put the autopsy report
and the bloodstain evidence...

24
00:01:27,030 --> 00:01:29,130
in two separate envelopes.

25
00:01:29,690 --> 00:01:31,930
If they took it, like you said,

26
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:34,770
they must have forced
the drawer open.

27
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:36,100
In the process,

28
00:01:36,100 --> 00:01:38,540
I think the envelope
with the blood evidence...

29
00:01:38,540 --> 00:01:39,970
slipped behind the drawer.

30
00:01:40,040 --> 00:01:42,910
So all they found
was the autopsy report.

31
00:01:42,970 --> 00:01:46,410
The envelope with the blood evidence
was stuck behind the drawer,

32
00:01:47,250 --> 00:01:51,180
and I believe it was returned to me
with my hospital belongings.

33
00:01:52,750 --> 00:01:54,720
How is that possible?

34
00:01:55,690 --> 00:01:59,560
After I found the evidence,
I tried everything to find you.

35
00:02:00,330 --> 00:02:04,030
I realized they missed the evidence
and was desperate to get it to you,

36
00:02:04,930 --> 00:02:07,800
but all I ever heard was
that you had died.

37
00:02:09,330 --> 00:02:11,470
And just like that,
over 20 years went by.

38
00:02:15,210 --> 00:02:16,240
Can...

39
00:02:16,370 --> 00:02:18,940
the blood evidence from back then
still be used?

40
00:02:20,110 --> 00:02:21,210
Absolutely.

41
00:02:22,250 --> 00:02:24,650
It weighed on my conscience,
so I kept it.

42
00:02:36,760 --> 00:02:38,330
(Ihwachae)

43
00:02:41,030 --> 00:02:44,140
I'll arrange to have my things
in the US shipped to Korea.

44
00:02:45,200 --> 00:02:46,700
With today's forensic technology,

45
00:02:46,700 --> 00:02:48,810
we can definitely
identify the killer.

46
00:02:52,980 --> 00:02:54,180
Thank you.

47
00:02:55,750 --> 00:02:57,150
Thank you, Doctor.

48
00:02:57,150 --> 00:02:58,280
My pleasure.

49
00:02:58,750 --> 00:03:01,150
If anything,
I'm worried I was too late.

50
00:03:02,620 --> 00:03:04,320
The statute of limitations
has expired,

51
00:03:04,320 --> 00:03:06,190
so legal action will be difficult.

52
00:03:06,820 --> 00:03:10,160
I always knew that legal action
would be out of the question.

53
00:03:11,300 --> 00:03:13,900
I've been preparing to make them pay
in my own way,

54
00:03:15,330 --> 00:03:16,730
and the evidence...

55
00:03:17,140 --> 00:03:19,340
will be my ace in the hole.

56
00:03:44,560 --> 00:03:46,030
Oh Jung Ran just showed up.

57
00:03:46,430 --> 00:03:49,300
You should probably leave first,
just in case, Doctor.

58
00:04:11,690 --> 00:04:13,420
Are you Mrs. Han,

59
00:04:13,960 --> 00:04:15,090
the owner here?

60
00:04:15,360 --> 00:04:16,830
I am.

61
00:04:17,860 --> 00:04:19,960
Are you looking
to have a hanbok tailored?

62
00:04:20,030 --> 00:04:23,170
Wouldn't you need an occasion first
to get one?

63
00:04:24,100 --> 00:04:25,170
You...

64
00:04:25,640 --> 00:04:28,610
The hanbok shop is just a side gig
for your matchmaking business.

65
00:04:28,710 --> 00:04:29,710
Maybe,

66
00:04:30,680 --> 00:04:34,580
but I'm afraid Ihwachae
is very selective about its clients.

67
00:04:34,710 --> 00:04:35,850
Selective?

68
00:04:36,950 --> 00:04:38,120
Selective, you say?

69
00:04:39,920 --> 00:04:42,320
I'm Oh Jung Ran,
the wife of Adele's chairman.

70
00:04:42,390 --> 00:04:43,660
You gave that tramp Kim Myung Hui...

71
00:04:43,660 --> 00:04:45,620
your gold card to invite her,

72
00:04:45,820 --> 00:04:47,030
even though
I'm the wife of Adele's chairman...

73
00:04:47,130 --> 00:04:48,860
and my son is the true heir.

74
00:04:50,530 --> 00:04:54,330
Match us with the family
you chose for her now.

75
00:04:55,530 --> 00:04:56,570
Better yet,

76
00:04:56,830 --> 00:05:00,040
match my son
with a superior family first.

77
00:05:00,100 --> 00:05:04,110
I invited Director Kim Myung Hui,
not you.

78
00:05:05,010 --> 00:05:07,180
I have no business with you, Ms. Oh,

79
00:05:07,780 --> 00:05:09,150
so please leave.

80
00:05:13,580 --> 00:05:14,590
What?

81
00:05:17,890 --> 00:05:19,290
Show our guest out.

82
00:05:21,930 --> 00:05:23,530
What's happening? What is this?

83
00:05:23,530 --> 00:05:25,100
Why are you doing this?

84
00:05:25,160 --> 00:05:27,370
Let go of me. Let go!

85
00:05:27,370 --> 00:05:28,730
Get your hands off me. Hey!

86
00:05:29,170 --> 00:05:30,440
I said, let go!

87
00:05:42,850 --> 00:05:45,680
(Profile: Kim Myung Hui)

88
00:05:50,250 --> 00:05:51,560
Please get back to me soon.

89
00:05:52,120 --> 00:05:55,490
All right. Once it's ready,
I'll have it delivered by Yoon Jung.

90
00:05:58,030 --> 00:05:59,200
One second.

91
00:06:01,230 --> 00:06:03,070
Is your daughter doing well?

92
00:06:03,840 --> 00:06:05,170
She is, thanks to you.

93
00:06:05,640 --> 00:06:07,440
And how is your nephew?

94
00:06:08,270 --> 00:06:09,970
- He's good.
- We can meet...

95
00:06:09,970 --> 00:06:11,710
once the proof from the US arrives.

96
00:06:12,380 --> 00:06:15,250
I'll need my daughter's help
to get the evidence back anyway.

97
00:06:16,010 --> 00:06:17,010
Her help?

98
00:06:18,950 --> 00:06:21,890
I plan to have the evidence sent
to my daughter's personal P.O. box.

99
00:06:22,290 --> 00:06:24,220
Since I travel so much for business,

100
00:06:24,560 --> 00:06:27,360
I started using it
to send her gifts.

101
00:06:29,160 --> 00:06:31,300
It's faster and more secure
than other services.

102
00:06:31,760 --> 00:06:35,170
You need a special key
to open the P.O. box,

103
00:06:35,500 --> 00:06:38,000
and there's also
a mandatory identity check.

104
00:06:38,540 --> 00:06:40,200
When the evidence arrives,

105
00:06:40,200 --> 00:06:42,140
my daughter will pick it up
from her box.

106
00:06:43,740 --> 00:06:46,610
I always wondered what she's like.

107
00:06:46,910 --> 00:06:48,450
I guess I'll get to meet her soon.

108
00:06:48,510 --> 00:06:51,550
After she receives the package,
let's meet up with the kids.

109
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:54,220
I'll be in touch then.

110
00:07:16,610 --> 00:07:18,680
I said, let go. Let go of me!

111
00:07:18,980 --> 00:07:20,040
You jerks!

112
00:07:20,510 --> 00:07:22,110
Do you have any idea who I am?

113
00:07:22,110 --> 00:07:23,510
How dare you drag me out?

114
00:07:23,780 --> 00:07:24,780
Jung Ran!

115
00:07:24,880 --> 00:07:26,820
- Let go of me.
- Get off her.

116
00:07:28,950 --> 00:07:30,890
I don't care
how established this place is.

117
00:07:31,490 --> 00:07:33,190
This is going too far.

118
00:07:35,790 --> 00:07:37,730
Hey!

119
00:07:37,730 --> 00:07:39,630
You won't even answer me?

120
00:07:41,430 --> 00:07:44,270
What trouble did you cause
this time?

121
00:07:44,340 --> 00:07:46,670
Why are you being so spineless?

122
00:07:46,770 --> 00:07:48,610
First you defend me,
and now you're nagging me...

123
00:07:48,670 --> 00:07:49,710
like you don't have a backbone.

124
00:07:49,770 --> 00:07:51,340
It's not that I have no backbone.

125
00:07:51,340 --> 00:07:52,910
I'm trying to save you some face.

126
00:07:52,910 --> 00:07:55,410
They'd respect you even less
if I called you out in public.

127
00:07:55,480 --> 00:07:58,950
Then you should've thrown a punch
instead of just flapping your gums.

128
00:08:00,320 --> 00:08:01,350
Those punks...

129
00:08:01,620 --> 00:08:02,890
got scared and ran off.

130
00:08:02,950 --> 00:08:04,860
Here, take this.

131
00:08:04,960 --> 00:08:07,860
Are you hurt? Let me see.

132
00:08:08,130 --> 00:08:09,430
What's there to see?

133
00:08:09,630 --> 00:08:11,600
- Let me see if you're hurt.
- Seriously?

134
00:08:12,100 --> 00:08:13,830
Once I have the evidence,

135
00:08:14,270 --> 00:08:16,730
I'll expose your crimes
to the world.

136
00:08:18,170 --> 00:08:21,870
Even Chairman Park won't be able
to make a killer's son his heir.

137
00:08:23,540 --> 00:08:26,110
That's how I'll take over
Adele Group,

138
00:08:26,740 --> 00:08:28,550
give it to Min Jun,

139
00:08:29,480 --> 00:08:31,280
and get justice for my sister.

140
00:08:34,090 --> 00:08:35,150
Once I do,

141
00:08:37,220 --> 00:08:39,320
will I finally be able to live...

142
00:08:40,320 --> 00:08:42,930
as Dan Hui again
instead of as my sister?

143
00:08:55,670 --> 00:08:59,910
Maybe I should have picked
a darker color for the strap.

144
00:09:00,180 --> 00:09:03,380
I'm afraid it's too much my taste.
Are you sure it's okay?

145
00:09:04,420 --> 00:09:05,450
I love it.

146
00:09:05,850 --> 00:09:08,290
Come on, don't just say that.

147
00:09:08,390 --> 00:09:10,550
I really mean it.

148
00:09:10,860 --> 00:09:14,130
It's a one-of-a-kind watch
that you made for me yourself.

149
00:09:14,790 --> 00:09:18,030
Plus, it's a matching watch,
so I love it twice as much.

150
00:09:19,700 --> 00:09:22,300
You know, when I become
a jewelry designer,

151
00:09:22,570 --> 00:09:26,370
I want to create unique jewelry
that's perfect for each client.

152
00:09:26,900 --> 00:09:28,810
Something that reflects...

153
00:09:28,810 --> 00:09:32,210
their story, their tastes,
and their dreams like a mirror.

154
00:09:33,740 --> 00:09:36,180
Sure, you'll definitely
be great at that.

155
00:09:36,750 --> 00:09:39,620
You've already captured our story
in this watch.

156
00:09:39,920 --> 00:09:43,490
Every time I look at it,
I get excited about our future.

157
00:09:43,890 --> 00:09:44,890
Me too.

158
00:09:45,620 --> 00:09:49,960
I wish we could
be together like this forever.

159
00:09:57,470 --> 00:10:00,570
All right, my turn.
How did you like my present?

160
00:10:02,840 --> 00:10:05,980
I'm sorry, I haven't opened it yet.

161
00:10:06,680 --> 00:10:07,680
Still?

162
00:10:08,610 --> 00:10:11,680
I promised my dad
I'd always open his first.

163
00:10:12,280 --> 00:10:13,520
Let's open it together.

164
00:10:23,590 --> 00:10:24,700
No way.

165
00:10:25,300 --> 00:10:27,030
That's my dad for you.

166
00:10:27,030 --> 00:10:29,430
How did he know I needed one?

167
00:10:35,140 --> 00:10:37,070
Look at this pearl.
Isn't it beautiful?

168
00:10:40,780 --> 00:10:42,650
Beautiful, yes.

169
00:10:45,280 --> 00:10:47,020
Seriously?

170
00:10:48,750 --> 00:10:49,950
Open my present next.

171
00:10:50,790 --> 00:10:51,790
All right.

172
00:11:01,700 --> 00:11:02,870
What's this?

173
00:11:03,370 --> 00:11:06,370
(University College of Business
and Management Birmingham)

174
00:11:08,410 --> 00:11:09,510
What is this?

175
00:11:09,770 --> 00:11:11,140
You're going to the UK too?

176
00:11:11,140 --> 00:11:12,910
Did you think I'd let you go alone?

177
00:11:13,610 --> 00:11:15,750
While you study jewelry design,

178
00:11:16,310 --> 00:11:19,350
I'll continue my business studies
at a university in the UK.

179
00:11:21,020 --> 00:11:22,420
And after we graduate...

180
00:11:27,690 --> 00:11:29,260
I'll surprise you...

181
00:11:30,360 --> 00:11:31,830
with an unforgettable proposal.

182
00:11:58,490 --> 00:12:00,860
(Adele Group New Design Competition)

183
00:12:02,530 --> 00:12:05,130
When on earth are they going
to announce the results?

184
00:12:07,200 --> 00:12:08,430
Baek Jin Ju...

185
00:12:08,830 --> 00:12:11,070
She's so smug about going to study
in the UK.

186
00:12:11,800 --> 00:12:14,170
I really need to win this
and knock her down a peg.

187
00:12:15,170 --> 00:12:16,770
This is so frustrating.

188
00:12:18,010 --> 00:12:19,010
Are you Choi Yu Na?

189
00:12:21,510 --> 00:12:22,950
Aren't you the guy from the library?

190
00:12:22,950 --> 00:12:25,450
Oh, right.

191
00:12:25,680 --> 00:12:26,720
Sorry to break it to you,

192
00:12:27,020 --> 00:12:29,020
but I'm not interested
in guys like you.

193
00:12:29,850 --> 00:12:32,320
Well, thank you.
The feeling's mutual.

194
00:12:32,390 --> 00:12:33,660
I'm only interested
in Baek Jin Ju anyway.

195
00:12:36,490 --> 00:12:37,630
Baek Jin Ju?

196
00:12:40,130 --> 00:12:42,730
I hear you're Baek Jin Ju's friend.
For a friend...

197
00:12:43,130 --> 00:12:44,140
who's like a brother,

198
00:12:44,200 --> 00:12:45,840
and a brother who's like a friend,

199
00:12:46,670 --> 00:12:49,170
I have a few things to confirm
about Baek Jin Ju.

200
00:12:49,340 --> 00:12:50,340
Whatever.

201
00:12:56,450 --> 00:12:58,550
Shoving people aside
is so natural to her.

202
00:12:58,550 --> 00:13:00,020
She's a natural-born...

203
00:13:00,780 --> 00:13:02,220
mean girl.

204
00:13:03,520 --> 00:13:05,890
Don't birds of a feather
flock together?

205
00:13:08,590 --> 00:13:10,690
Does that mean Baek Jin Ju
is just as nasty?

206
00:13:11,700 --> 00:13:12,760
Forget it.

207
00:13:13,400 --> 00:13:15,570
Digging around for dirt
isn't really my style.

208
00:13:16,430 --> 00:13:19,440
If I want to know something,
I'll go straight to the source.

209
00:13:27,580 --> 00:13:28,980
What are you doing in my room?

210
00:13:30,750 --> 00:13:33,650
What does it look like?
I was waiting for you.

211
00:13:37,220 --> 00:13:39,820
I found out
something very interesting.

212
00:13:40,220 --> 00:13:42,230
My elective classroom changed,

213
00:13:42,230 --> 00:13:45,030
so I got lost in the annex,
and bam...

214
00:13:48,370 --> 00:13:49,500
I saw you with your girlfriend.

215
00:13:52,600 --> 00:13:53,700
Pretend you didn't see anything.

216
00:13:55,640 --> 00:13:56,710
I'm asking you.

217
00:13:57,810 --> 00:13:58,810
Are you...

218
00:13:59,440 --> 00:14:00,540
asking me...

219
00:14:00,740 --> 00:14:01,750
for a favor?

220
00:14:03,150 --> 00:14:05,380
After I tried so hard
to get close to you,

221
00:14:05,380 --> 00:14:07,380
and you lumped me in with Ms. Oh...

222
00:14:07,450 --> 00:14:09,520
and tried to get rid of us,
you're asking me...

223
00:14:09,520 --> 00:14:10,590
for a favor?

224
00:14:10,590 --> 00:14:11,860
How dare you?

225
00:14:13,590 --> 00:14:14,760
You must be serious about her.

226
00:14:15,490 --> 00:14:16,490
Right?

227
00:14:17,490 --> 00:14:18,800
So...

228
00:14:20,160 --> 00:14:22,000
is that why you pulled
a stunt like this?

229
00:14:23,600 --> 00:14:24,870
(University College of Business
and Management Birmingham)

230
00:14:29,910 --> 00:14:33,080
With your brains, Min Jun,
you obviously got accepted.

231
00:14:33,140 --> 00:14:35,950
The question is,
can you get past this family?

232
00:14:35,950 --> 00:14:37,150
No, that's not it.

233
00:14:37,410 --> 00:14:40,020
It's whether you can
persuade your mom.

234
00:14:41,720 --> 00:14:43,920
Wasn't your mom completely
against you studying abroad?

235
00:14:44,560 --> 00:14:48,660
Remember? It's the reason
you gave up studying in the US.

236
00:14:49,630 --> 00:14:50,890
I'm going this time.

237
00:14:51,030 --> 00:14:52,400
Exactly.

238
00:14:52,800 --> 00:14:55,330
And that's the key right there.

239
00:14:56,200 --> 00:15:01,010
The reason an obedient mama's boy
would suddenly pull such a stunt.

240
00:15:09,450 --> 00:15:11,350
Is Baek Jin Ju studying
in the UK too?

241
00:15:12,750 --> 00:15:14,220
How do you know Jin Ju?

242
00:15:14,720 --> 00:15:16,990
Hey, I'm popular at our school.

243
00:15:17,090 --> 00:15:19,220
It's not hard to find that out.

244
00:15:19,290 --> 00:15:21,290
I heard she's a design major,

245
00:15:22,490 --> 00:15:24,560
and she seems like a total brat...

246
00:15:24,560 --> 00:15:25,560
Says who?

247
00:15:28,370 --> 00:15:30,300
I've never seen you this angry.

248
00:15:30,930 --> 00:15:34,410
Is this the Baek Jin Ju effect?

249
00:15:36,210 --> 00:15:37,640
You like her that much?

250
00:15:37,940 --> 00:15:40,110
Why? What's so great about her?

251
00:15:41,180 --> 00:15:42,180
Darn.

252
00:15:44,320 --> 00:15:46,350
Fine. If you don't want
to talk about it, don't.

253
00:15:46,820 --> 00:15:49,620
- I'll find out myself.
- Hey!

254
00:15:51,120 --> 00:15:52,120
What?

255
00:15:52,660 --> 00:15:53,660
I just...

256
00:15:56,390 --> 00:15:57,390
I just like her.

257
00:15:59,660 --> 00:16:01,030
You don't sound
very convinced yourself.

258
00:16:01,130 --> 00:16:03,670
I've never really thought about
why I like her.

259
00:16:04,170 --> 00:16:05,800
All that matters to me...

260
00:16:06,670 --> 00:16:08,270
is that I want to be with her.

261
00:16:10,340 --> 00:16:11,840
Because I want to be with her,

262
00:16:12,680 --> 00:16:15,250
I'm starting to picture
a different future for myself.

263
00:16:16,780 --> 00:16:18,450
That's why I'm trying
to get past them.

264
00:16:18,720 --> 00:16:20,780
The hurdles in this house,
and our father.

265
00:16:21,550 --> 00:16:22,590
Your mom too?

266
00:16:26,220 --> 00:16:27,420
I'm going to try and convince her.

267
00:16:28,290 --> 00:16:29,290
Somehow.

268
00:16:41,770 --> 00:16:44,240
Park Min Jun really has it bad.

269
00:16:44,980 --> 00:16:47,640
And that just makes me
even more curious.

270
00:16:48,610 --> 00:16:50,180
Baek Jin Ju.

271
00:17:03,630 --> 00:17:04,630
Looks delicious, doesn't it?

272
00:17:07,430 --> 00:17:08,730
- Ms. Hong.
- Yes?

273
00:17:08,730 --> 00:17:11,940
- Could you taste this for me?
- Sure. Of course.

274
00:17:19,340 --> 00:17:20,640
It's lightly seasoned,

275
00:17:20,640 --> 00:17:22,850
which is perfect for your dad.

276
00:17:22,850 --> 00:17:24,950
I know what my dad likes.

277
00:17:25,750 --> 00:17:26,780
You sure do.

278
00:17:27,650 --> 00:17:30,890
You must be so excited
to see your father after so long.

279
00:17:31,190 --> 00:17:35,830
Yes. Whenever he's about to visit,
I get as excited as a little kid.

280
00:17:35,830 --> 00:17:37,390
Of course you do.

281
00:17:38,630 --> 00:17:41,030
It's just the two of you,

282
00:17:41,030 --> 00:17:42,800
so of course
you have a special bond.

283
00:17:43,370 --> 00:17:44,800
- That's not true.
- What?

284
00:17:44,800 --> 00:17:48,010
You, Mr. Choi, and Yu Na
are family to me too.

285
00:17:48,810 --> 00:17:50,940
What? Oh...

286
00:17:50,940 --> 00:17:52,940
Right, of course.

287
00:17:53,110 --> 00:17:56,080
After all these years
we've spent together?

288
00:17:56,250 --> 00:17:58,020
Of course we're family.

289
00:17:58,020 --> 00:17:59,380
You sweet girl.

290
00:18:02,390 --> 00:18:06,920
CEO Baek will be here any minute,
so hurry up and get ready.

291
00:18:07,460 --> 00:18:09,590
Here, give me your apron.

292
00:18:09,590 --> 00:18:11,500
That's right. Go on now.

293
00:18:11,500 --> 00:18:12,900
- Okay.
- Go on.

294
00:18:20,700 --> 00:18:22,870
What's with all the fuss?

295
00:18:24,410 --> 00:18:25,440
For goodness' sake.

296
00:18:25,740 --> 00:18:28,250
You don't know anything,
so keep quiet.

297
00:18:28,250 --> 00:18:30,350
We have to put together
a big meal...

298
00:18:30,610 --> 00:18:31,820
to show him...

299
00:18:31,820 --> 00:18:33,980
that we've been taking
good care of Jin Ju,

300
00:18:34,080 --> 00:18:37,290
and that all the money
he sends for her every month...

301
00:18:37,350 --> 00:18:39,020
was spent on her.

302
00:18:39,260 --> 00:18:41,160
We have to prove that to CEO Baek.

303
00:18:41,930 --> 00:18:43,760
You're really laying it on thick.

304
00:18:44,190 --> 00:18:46,800
If you get it, back me up.

305
00:18:46,800 --> 00:18:48,800
Say she had the warmest room,

306
00:18:48,870 --> 00:18:52,000
and that we gave her
the best food and clothes.

307
00:18:52,270 --> 00:18:54,970
That's the story we're sticking to.
Got it?

308
00:18:57,770 --> 00:19:00,640
Do you hear me? Unbelievable.

309
00:19:01,610 --> 00:19:02,610
My goodness.

310
00:19:03,310 --> 00:19:05,650
- Jin Ju.
- Dad!

311
00:19:05,720 --> 00:19:06,820
Hey.

312
00:19:07,890 --> 00:19:09,750
Welcome. It's good to see you.

313
00:19:09,750 --> 00:19:11,190
You too. Have you been well?

314
00:19:11,260 --> 00:19:13,890
I've been working so hard
I haven't had a moment to breathe.

315
00:19:14,590 --> 00:19:15,930
- I see.
- Goodness.

316
00:19:15,930 --> 00:19:17,590
Absolutely.

317
00:19:17,590 --> 00:19:20,860
You put him in charge
of the entire Korean branch.

318
00:19:20,860 --> 00:19:23,170
We can't have people gossiping...

319
00:19:23,230 --> 00:19:25,640
that he got the job
because you're hometown friends.

320
00:19:26,240 --> 00:19:29,870
We're determined to repay
your faith in us, CEO Baek,

321
00:19:29,940 --> 00:19:31,480
and we've been working
our butts off...

322
00:19:32,710 --> 00:19:33,710
Goodness.

323
00:19:34,610 --> 00:19:39,180
I mean, we're working very hard
is what I was trying to say.

324
00:19:39,950 --> 00:19:40,980
I see.

325
00:19:43,090 --> 00:19:46,490
Come on.
Let's grab some dinner first.

326
00:19:46,620 --> 00:19:47,930
It's been a while,

327
00:19:47,930 --> 00:19:50,230
so the two of us
should grab a drink.

328
00:19:50,230 --> 00:19:51,730
- Of course.
- Let's go.

329
00:19:56,200 --> 00:19:57,530
Friends? As if.

330
00:19:58,100 --> 00:20:00,040
Who grovels to a friend?

331
00:20:07,640 --> 00:20:10,010
I'm sorry I haven't been in touch
since leaving my daughter with you.

332
00:20:11,010 --> 00:20:13,550
Thank you for everything
you've done for Jin Ju.

333
00:20:14,120 --> 00:20:16,090
What trouble?

334
00:20:16,350 --> 00:20:20,160
Since starting college,
she's handled everything on her own.

335
00:20:20,520 --> 00:20:22,230
We barely had to lift a finger.

336
00:20:27,130 --> 00:20:31,670
That doesn't mean
we didn't worry about her.

337
00:20:31,940 --> 00:20:36,610
We were like family back in the US,
so it just felt natural.

338
00:20:36,910 --> 00:20:40,910
Still, Jin Ju's been responsible
since coming to Korea for college.

339
00:20:40,910 --> 00:20:42,580
That's basically what he's saying.

340
00:20:43,810 --> 00:20:45,580
Right, honey?

341
00:20:46,050 --> 00:20:48,920
Yes, exactly. That's what I meant.

342
00:20:49,550 --> 00:20:51,620
We all know how smart Jin Ju is.

343
00:20:51,620 --> 00:20:54,120
She excelled in the US
and is doing great in Korea too.

344
00:20:54,360 --> 00:20:55,690
I just wish our Yu Na...

345
00:20:56,560 --> 00:20:58,960
could be half as dedicated
as she is.

346
00:20:59,030 --> 00:21:00,460
Dad, just drop it!

347
00:21:00,860 --> 00:21:01,870
Goodness.

348
00:21:02,630 --> 00:21:03,630
Oh, dear.

349
00:21:08,310 --> 00:21:11,480
Yu Na actually helped me a lot.

350
00:21:11,810 --> 00:21:15,980
I couldn't have done well in college
or prepared to go abroad on my own.

351
00:21:16,550 --> 00:21:18,220
Yes, of course!

352
00:21:18,550 --> 00:21:21,420
You're as kind as you are smart,
aren't you?

353
00:21:26,020 --> 00:21:27,390
What the...

354
00:21:28,560 --> 00:21:29,730
Goodness, Yu Na.

355
00:21:29,730 --> 00:21:31,230
Does she need to go to the bathroom?

356
00:21:31,230 --> 00:21:32,300
That brat.

357
00:21:33,130 --> 00:21:34,830
She must not be feeling well.

358
00:21:36,100 --> 00:21:38,370
- Anyway, it's not much, but...
- Come on, dig in.

359
00:21:38,440 --> 00:21:41,270
- Thank you.
- Let's eat. All right.

360
00:21:42,870 --> 00:21:45,340
Just unbelievable.

361
00:21:45,340 --> 00:21:46,780
Yu Na, that brat.

362
00:21:47,440 --> 00:21:49,450
They say the crazier you act,
the harder you fall.

363
00:21:49,450 --> 00:21:50,610
Honestly.

364
00:21:50,780 --> 00:21:53,020
I went to all this trouble
setting the table,

365
00:21:53,020 --> 00:21:54,150
and she pulls that?

366
00:21:54,220 --> 00:21:56,550
- Goodness.
- You were way worse.

367
00:21:57,590 --> 00:21:58,990
What? What did I do?

368
00:21:59,120 --> 00:22:01,830
And what about you
and your phony posh accent?

369
00:22:02,030 --> 00:22:03,360
"Right, honey?"

370
00:22:04,590 --> 00:22:05,600
Give me a break.

371
00:22:05,860 --> 00:22:08,570
Forcing that accent
just makes you sound cheap.

372
00:22:09,170 --> 00:22:12,140
I was so embarrassed for you
in front of Jun Gi.

373
00:22:12,640 --> 00:22:16,310
Being coy only works
if you can actually pull it off.

374
00:22:16,970 --> 00:22:17,970
Why you...

375
00:22:19,080 --> 00:22:21,040
Just forget it.

376
00:22:21,480 --> 00:22:23,880
I'm sophisticated, classy...

377
00:22:23,880 --> 00:22:25,480
You, classy? Don't make me laugh.

378
00:22:25,650 --> 00:22:27,520
You worthless piece of work.
Honestly.

379
00:22:27,880 --> 00:22:29,690
Look at you running
that filthy mouth of yours.

380
00:22:29,790 --> 00:22:31,620
Do you want me
to grab a sledgehammer...

381
00:22:31,620 --> 00:22:33,220
and crack your head open?

382
00:22:33,290 --> 00:22:36,430
Hey, you don't have to go that far.

383
00:22:37,030 --> 00:22:39,660
Why do you always have to be
so extreme?

384
00:22:39,830 --> 00:22:43,000
A sledgehammer?
For someone as elegant as you?

385
00:22:43,870 --> 00:22:48,270
Honey, don't think
like that again. Okay?

386
00:22:48,340 --> 00:22:49,670
Let go of me.

387
00:22:49,670 --> 00:22:52,240
Whatever. Just go find Yu Na.

388
00:22:52,680 --> 00:22:54,810
Once Jin Ju leaves for the UK,

389
00:22:55,050 --> 00:22:57,080
the monthly payments will stop.

390
00:22:57,080 --> 00:22:59,480
What if you lose
your executive position after that?

391
00:22:59,550 --> 00:23:00,820
That'd be bad for us.

392
00:23:01,990 --> 00:23:05,190
We must at least smooth things over
before CEO Baek leaves.

393
00:23:05,690 --> 00:23:09,490
Forget it. We don't have to tiptoe
around that guy anymore.

394
00:23:11,390 --> 00:23:13,530
I've got my own plans in the works.

395
00:23:15,970 --> 00:23:17,400
What's that all about?

396
00:23:19,400 --> 00:23:22,240
Wait, so I'm moving out
of Yu Na's house?

397
00:23:22,640 --> 00:23:25,380
It'd be nice to spend time together
before I leave.

398
00:23:26,610 --> 00:23:30,410
But why won't you let me say
a proper goodbye before I leave?

399
00:23:31,650 --> 00:23:33,080
About that...

400
00:23:34,120 --> 00:23:36,120
I'll explain everything to you
in due time.

401
00:23:36,750 --> 00:23:37,750
Okay?

402
00:23:37,950 --> 00:23:38,960
Sure.

403
00:23:41,220 --> 00:23:44,230
Can I at least tell my boyfriend?

404
00:23:44,960 --> 00:23:47,500
Min Jun always picks me up
and drops me off.

405
00:23:48,230 --> 00:23:51,740
I should probably let him know
I'm staying at the hotel with you.

406
00:23:53,770 --> 00:23:55,240
Has that punk been that good to you?

407
00:23:55,810 --> 00:23:58,640
Dad, his name's Min Jun,
not some punk.

408
00:24:01,650 --> 00:24:03,280
And...

409
00:24:04,250 --> 00:24:07,020
Min Jun is going
to study abroad with me...

410
00:24:07,680 --> 00:24:08,790
at a school in the UK.

411
00:24:10,250 --> 00:24:11,250
Really?

412
00:24:12,320 --> 00:24:15,860
Then, I'd like to meet him
before I go.

413
00:24:16,730 --> 00:24:19,300
If he's going with you,
I should at least say hi.

414
00:24:21,630 --> 00:24:23,370
- Go on in.
- Okay.

415
00:24:43,320 --> 00:24:44,490
What was that about?

416
00:24:44,860 --> 00:24:47,460
What do you mean?

417
00:24:47,460 --> 00:24:48,460
Park Min Jun.

418
00:24:49,960 --> 00:24:52,600
Is Park Min Jun moving to the UK
to study too?

419
00:24:53,400 --> 00:24:54,530
Him too?

420
00:24:56,030 --> 00:24:57,530
Is he going with you?

421
00:25:00,370 --> 00:25:01,370
Yes.

422
00:25:18,620 --> 00:25:20,660
Choi Yu Na, you brat.

423
00:25:21,360 --> 00:25:23,160
Let me study in the UK too.

424
00:25:23,260 --> 00:25:25,200
What? The UK?

425
00:25:25,500 --> 00:25:27,430
Is it just because Jin Ju is going?

426
00:25:27,430 --> 00:25:28,600
You'll let me, right?

427
00:25:29,730 --> 00:25:30,800
What about tuition?

428
00:25:31,530 --> 00:25:33,170
How much is tuition per year
in the UK?

429
00:25:33,170 --> 00:25:34,770
Can't you do that for me, Dad?

430
00:25:36,140 --> 00:25:39,640
Honestly, why would you need
to study abroad?

431
00:25:40,240 --> 00:25:41,680
Jin Ju might, but you...

432
00:25:41,680 --> 00:25:43,350
Jin Ju this, Jin Ju that!

433
00:25:44,080 --> 00:25:46,280
Dad, why are you always
comparing me to her?

434
00:25:46,580 --> 00:25:47,680
You think I keep quiet
because I don't know...

435
00:25:47,680 --> 00:25:48,790
how to compare you to other parents?

436
00:25:49,020 --> 00:25:50,020
What...

437
00:25:50,090 --> 00:25:51,320
CEO Baek...

438
00:25:51,690 --> 00:25:54,520
would do anything for his daughter,
even send her abroad to study.

439
00:25:56,130 --> 00:25:58,260
But you can't even give me
the one thing I ask for.

440
00:25:58,600 --> 00:26:01,130
You're not as successful
as him, so how...

441
00:26:01,130 --> 00:26:02,170
My goodness.

442
00:26:03,230 --> 00:26:04,500
How am I the only disappointment
in this house?

443
00:26:05,870 --> 00:26:08,570
Why do you always put me down? Why?

444
00:26:13,480 --> 00:26:14,910
I can't believe that brat.

445
00:26:21,520 --> 00:26:24,750
I guess I've been making things hard
for Yu Na all this time.

446
00:26:25,760 --> 00:26:28,530
Maybe that's why Dad...

447
00:26:35,300 --> 00:26:36,300
Choi Yu Na!

448
00:26:37,500 --> 00:26:38,500
Good grief.

449
00:26:40,000 --> 00:26:41,740
How could you say
something like that?

450
00:26:42,240 --> 00:26:44,210
You get so defensive
the second Jin Ju is mentioned.

451
00:26:46,780 --> 00:26:49,610
Couldn't you have just let it go
on a day like today?

452
00:26:49,980 --> 00:26:51,010
A day like today?

453
00:26:51,750 --> 00:26:53,850
So I have to tiptoe
around Baek Jin Ju forever?

454
00:26:54,550 --> 00:26:56,290
So what if you have to?

455
00:26:56,820 --> 00:26:59,620
Who do you think pays for your food
and the clothes on your back?

456
00:27:00,160 --> 00:27:04,030
People need to care more
about practical benefits than pride.

457
00:27:04,230 --> 00:27:06,030
If that's how you're going to talk,
then leave.

458
00:27:06,030 --> 00:27:08,030
I don't need this, so just get out!

459
00:27:08,600 --> 00:27:10,430
Good grief. Honestly.

460
00:27:12,800 --> 00:27:14,700
If you want to study abroad
that badly,

461
00:27:16,870 --> 00:27:17,870
go ahead and start preparing.

462
00:27:18,480 --> 00:27:21,680
I'll figure out
how to get the money to send you.

463
00:27:24,280 --> 00:27:26,480
What do you mean by that?

464
00:27:26,850 --> 00:27:28,950
Do you think I'm going
to spend the rest of my life...

465
00:27:29,220 --> 00:27:30,950
sucking up to them?

466
00:27:31,620 --> 00:27:35,160
I've been securing
our family's piece of the pie,

467
00:27:36,030 --> 00:27:37,030
so just you wait.

468
00:27:53,940 --> 00:27:57,850
That's right.
Practicality is what matters most.

469
00:27:59,850 --> 00:28:03,320
I'm done sucking up to the Baeks.

470
00:28:08,020 --> 00:28:09,160
It's done.

471
00:28:09,430 --> 00:28:11,900
(Adele Group)

472
00:28:14,700 --> 00:28:18,300
James, I need you to personally
pack it up and send it.

473
00:28:19,500 --> 00:28:22,240
Yes, the box
containing the red pearl.

474
00:28:22,940 --> 00:28:24,440
Of course, sir.

475
00:28:24,540 --> 00:28:26,740
How did things go in Korea?

476
00:28:27,880 --> 00:28:30,080
I've confirmed everything,
and I've made up my mind.

477
00:28:31,580 --> 00:28:33,320
Now it's time to settle things
once and for all.

478
00:28:39,760 --> 00:28:43,130
I can't believe the Adele family
was behind that incident.

479
00:28:44,330 --> 00:28:45,930
And now this on top of everything.

480
00:28:48,830 --> 00:28:51,570
What a complicated
and twisted fate we share.

481
00:28:59,480 --> 00:29:02,080
- The car is ready, ma'am.
- Right.

482
00:29:03,050 --> 00:29:06,750
A meeting at Ihwachae for Min Jun?
It has to be about his marriage.

483
00:29:08,080 --> 00:29:09,490
It's not the right time yet.

484
00:29:09,990 --> 00:29:12,290
Once Dr. Baek's evidence arrives,
we'll have our hands full.

485
00:29:12,790 --> 00:29:13,890
Of course.

486
00:29:14,690 --> 00:29:16,860
I just hope Ihwachae doesn't
hold it against us...

487
00:29:17,230 --> 00:29:18,730
for lending us the venue last time.

488
00:29:30,640 --> 00:29:32,080
Find out where she's going.

489
00:29:32,710 --> 00:29:33,710
Yes, sir.

490
00:29:34,810 --> 00:29:36,950
And it's about time
you brought in the other party.

491
00:29:37,650 --> 00:29:38,650
Yes, sir.

492
00:29:53,730 --> 00:29:57,170
I've prepared the documents
exactly as you instructed, sir.

493
00:29:58,030 --> 00:29:59,640
There won't be any issues
with the merger and acquisition,

494
00:30:00,240 --> 00:30:01,940
and I've even drawn up
a secret contract...

495
00:30:02,810 --> 00:30:06,140
to make it easier for you
to embezzle the funds.

496
00:30:10,980 --> 00:30:13,680
So, on top of the money
we agreed on,

497
00:30:14,350 --> 00:30:16,150
you're also demanding Adele stock?

498
00:30:17,350 --> 00:30:21,120
Please, try to see it
from my position.

499
00:30:21,520 --> 00:30:24,960
I'm betraying a hometown friend
and a business partner of 15 years,

500
00:30:25,700 --> 00:30:29,330
selling his company out
from under him.

501
00:30:30,200 --> 00:30:33,570
I'm going to have to spend years
on the run from him.

502
00:30:34,640 --> 00:30:36,440
Living on the run,

503
00:30:37,810 --> 00:30:39,710
I'm bound to run out
of money eventually.

504
00:30:40,340 --> 00:30:44,210
Having some stock is the only way
this will be worth my while.

505
00:30:48,620 --> 00:30:51,590
I'm not asking for much.

506
00:30:52,760 --> 00:30:54,520
If you'd just give it
a little more thought,

507
00:30:55,160 --> 00:30:56,860
the deal will go off
without a hitch...

508
00:30:58,190 --> 00:30:59,430
The deal is off.

509
00:31:00,130 --> 00:31:01,130
What...

510
00:31:08,640 --> 00:31:11,110
There will be no deal whatsoever
with Adele Group.

511
00:31:51,780 --> 00:31:54,720
(Pearl in Red)

512
00:31:54,880 --> 00:31:57,850
What if that Kim Myung Hui manages
to marry her son into a good family?

513
00:31:58,020 --> 00:32:00,760
That can't happen.
I must stop her, no matter the cost.

514
00:32:01,020 --> 00:32:02,030
Studying abroad isn't an option.

515
00:32:02,130 --> 00:32:04,930
I'm a grown man.
I don't need your permission.

516
00:32:05,130 --> 00:32:08,230
Sorry. It's the director's orders,
so my hands are tied.

517
00:32:08,430 --> 00:32:09,830
I need you to meet Jin Ju for me.

518
00:32:10,200 --> 00:32:12,040
Me? You want me to meet Baek Jin Ju?

519
00:32:12,200 --> 00:32:14,440
You want me to beg Baek Jin Ju?

520
00:32:14,440 --> 00:32:16,470
- I'd rather die.
